        best_for: ['Casual digital artists seeking granular control', 'Social media managers creating complex, stylized thumbnails', 'Tabletop RPG (D&D) players generating highly specific maps and characters', 'Users intimidated by the technical complexity of local Stable Diffusion interfaces (Automatic1111)'],
        pros: ['The infinite "Canvas" environment is a massive paradigm shift, allowing for surgical, element-by-element image construction rather than rolling the dice on a single, massive prompt', 'It provides access to the raw power of customized Stable Diffusion models entirely in the browser, completely bypassing the need for a $2000 graphics card', 'The community discovery feed is incredibly useful; hovering over any image reveals the exact prompt and seed used, providing an instant masterclass in prompt engineering', 'The proprietary Playground models regularly rival Midjourney in photorealism and stylistic flair, often with vastly better understanding of spatial prompts'],
